		<div id="comment_body_64338625"><p>So these guys claim to not only have managed to create aneutronic nuclear fusion (practically a side note) they've managed to build it into a sexy little thruster unit?</p><p>Tell ITER they should just pack it in, job is done.</p><p>Someone should update wiki, which asserts "...the conditions required to harness aneutronic fusion are much more extreme than those required for deuterium-tritium fusion such as at ITER. "</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64338625">

